cb566a76-67ec-453e-a32e-5b6f589d8c1a	a1111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111	a153634f-5071-410f-b334-757b2746d58c	CET	A tuning fork of frequency 480 Hz is used with a resonance tube. First resonance at 17.5 cm, second at 52.5 cm. Speed of sound is:	330 m/s	336 m/s	340 m/s	350 m/s	C	lambda = 2(L2 - L1) = 2(52.5 - 17.5) cm = 70 cm = 0.70 m. v = f*lambda = 480 * 0.70 = 336 m/s. Closest: 336 m/s. Correct answer B.	60	f	\N	t	2026-06-05 11:51:50.387703	1	1
