795ab01d-1521-42e8-9556-835b7873364a	b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222	2a312e24-6628-4311-a6d6-4a90e8c515de	CET	Supercritical CO2 is used as a green solvent because:	It is highly toxic	It has tunable solvent properties and leaves no residue	It reacts with all organic compounds	It has very high viscosity	B	Supercritical CO2 (above 31.1 deg C and 73.8 atm) has gas-like diffusivity and liquid-like solvating power. It is non-toxic, non-flammable, leaves no residue (evaporates on pressure release), and its properties are tunable. Used in decaffeination of coffee, dry cleaning, and pharmaceutical processing.	60	f	\N	t	2026-06-05 03:04:52.728864	1	1
