b0c1a5ea-9eb5-4632-8386-8f7a4b1d71d7	b2222222-2222-2222-2222-222222222222	13aa8290-9ee6-433e-b1a7-5521641fa088	ABOVE_CET	Beryllium chloride (BeCl2) in the vapour phase exists as a monomer with sp hybridization. In the solid state it forms a chain polymer. What is the hybridization of Be in solid BeCl2?	sp	sp2	sp3	sp3d	C	In solid BeCl2, each Be is bridged by two Cl atoms using lone pairs from Cl to fill Be empty orbitals, forming a chain polymer: -[Cl-Be-Cl]n-. Each Be has 4 bonds (2 normal + 2 coordinate from Cl lone pairs) = sp3 hybridization (tetrahedral). In vapor (monomer): sp (linear). In dimer: sp2.	60	f	\N	t	2026-06-12 10:01:16.564709	1	1
